   "user": "Omar Shehata",
   "message": "> Not sure how threatening him would achieve that.\n\nit would counteract this:\n\n> the external collective he is part of is pressuring him in the wrong way\n\nthe simple way to understand it is imagine if:\n\n- Bob hurt Alice\n- Bob feels bad, tells his friends about the situation\n- Bob's friends want to make him feel better, they say \"screw Alice, you did the best you could do\"\n- Bob knows it's not true, but it would take a lot of friction/effort to admit this, push back on his friends, and fix the situation. It's EASIER to leave things as they are for now, and wait for things to resolve themselves",
