   "message": "> He tends to push out the thinker behind ideas he takes.\n\nhe doesn't always do this intentionally. Sometimes he's not aware who gave him the idea, and,\n\nthis is important:\n\n- he needs to \"dumb it down\" so that he can understand it. So he has to take it, repackage it (or sometimes you have to say it many times before he gets it). Once he gets it it \"feels his\" (because he worked hard to be able to get it/had to change it to make it \"fit\")",
